{"article_id":"7kzIZs7iteLzkBV5","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A seemingly divided Supreme Court on Tuesday heard highly anticipated cases on whether federal civil rights law should apply to LGBTQ people ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"with Chief Justice John Roberts questioning","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"how doing so would affect employers .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"In the first of two cases , the justices heard arguments","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"on whether a federal law","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"banning job discrimination on the basis of sex","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"should also protect sexual orientation .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Lower courts have split on the issue .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"A related case on transgender employees was also being heard Tuesday .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Roberts , a possible swing vote in the cases , wondered about the implications of what he described as an expansion of the job-discrimination law .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"`` If we 're going to be expanding the definition of what 'sex ' covers ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"what do we do about that issue ? ''","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Roberts asked .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Justice Neil Gorsuch said","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"the case seems close .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"He wondered","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"whether the justices should consider `` the massive social upheaval ''","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that might follow a ruling in favor of LGBTQ employees .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Justice Samuel Alito , a conservative , suggested","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that the high court would be usurping the role of Congress","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"by reading protection for sexual orientation into the 1964 Civil Rights Act ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"when lawmakers at the time likely envisioned","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"they were doing no such thing .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"`` You 're trying to change the meaning of 'sex , ' ''","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Justice Elena Kagan , a liberal , suggested","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"sexual orientation is a clear subset of sex discrimination ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that a man","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"who loves other men","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"can not be treated differently by an employer than a woman","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"who loves men .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"The cases Tuesday are the court 's first on LGBTQ rights since Justice Anthony Kennedy 's retirement and replacement by Justice Brett Kavanaugh .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"Kennedy upheld gay rights as the author of the landmark ruling in 2015","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"that made same-sex marriage legal throughout the United States .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Kavanaugh generally is regarded as more conservative .","depth":3},{"id":36,"text":"Members of the U.S. Supreme Court .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"Front row , left to right :","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Stephen Breyer , Clarence Thomas , Chief Justice John Roberts , Ruth Bader Ginsburg and Samuel Alito Jr.","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Back row , left to right :","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"Neil Gorsuch , Sonia Sotomayor , Elena Kagan and Brett Kavanaugh .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Getty","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"A decision is expected by early summer 2020 , amid the presidential election campaign .","depth":3},{"id":43,"text":"A ruling for employees","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"who were fired","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"because of their sexual orientation or gender identity","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"would have a big impact for the estimated 8.1 million LGBTQ workers across the country","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"because most states do n't protect them from workplace discrimination .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"An estimated 11.3 million U.S. adults identify as LGBTQ ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"according to the Williams Institute at the UCLA law school .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"The Trump administration has changed course from the Obama administration","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"and now supports employers","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"in arguing","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"that the civil rights law 's Title 7 does not prohibit discrimination","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"because of sexual orientation or transgender status .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"People waited in line outside the court since the weekend","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"to try to snag the few seats","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"the court makes available to the public for arguments .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"The justices were first hearing appeals in lawsuits","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"filed by Gerald Lynn Bostock ,","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"who claims","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"he lost his job","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"working for Clayton County , Georgia ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"after he began playing in a gay recreational softball league .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"He lost his case in federal district court and at the 11th U.S . Circuit Court of Appeals in Atlanta .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Skydiving instructor Donald Zarda was fired","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"shortly after telling a woman","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"he was preparing to take on a dive","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"that he was gay .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Zarda ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"who worked for Altitude Express on New York 's Long Island ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"he would sometimes reveal his sexual orientation","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"to allay concerns","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"women might have","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"about being strapped together during a dive .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Zarda initially lost his lawsuit ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"but the 2nd U.S . Circuit Court of Appeals ruled for him .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Zarda died in a wingsuit accident in Switzerland in 2014 .","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"His husband Bill Moore told chief legal correspondent Jan Crawford","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"that Zarda suffered from depression","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"after he was fired","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"and started doing jumps with greater risks .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"that Don would have died","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"had he not lost his job , ''","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"Moore said .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"`` I think","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"that he would have continued working summers and skydiving","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"and doing tandems","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"and would not have been taking this crazy trip to Europe in the middle of the summer ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"so I think","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"that him being fired is eventually what took his life . ''","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"Supreme Court weighs first LGBTQ cases since Justice Anthony Kennedy 's retirement","depth":4},{"id":94,"text":"The other case involves fired transgender funeral home director Aimee Stephens .","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"She lost her job","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"when she told Thomas Rost , owner of the Detroit-area R.G . and G.R . Harris Funeral Homes ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"that she had struggled with gender identity issues almost her whole life .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"Stephens was planning to exchange the dark suit and tie","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"she had worn","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"to work for nearly six years as an embalmer and funeral director","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"for a conservative dress or skirt","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"that was required for women","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"who worked for Rost .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Rost told Stephens","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"her plan would n't work","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"and let her go .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"The federal Equal Employment Opportunity Commission sued on her behalf","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"and ,","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"after losing in a district court ,","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"won a ruling in the 6th U.S . Circuit Court of Appeals in Cincinnati .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"During the Obama years , the commission had changed its longstanding interpretation of civil rights law","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"to include discrimination against LGBTQ people .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"In 2017 , the CBSN Originals documentary `` Gender | The Space Between '' took a deep dive into the complexities of gender identity and gender expression .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"Federal law prohibits discrimination","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"because of sex ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"but has no specific protection for sexual orientation or gender identity .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"The Trump administration and the employers say","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Congress could easily settle the matter","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"by amending Title 7","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"to include LGBTQ people .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Legislation to that effect is pending in Congress","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"but is not likely to pass the Republican-controlled Senate .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"But the workers contend ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"and the lower courts","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"that have ruled for them","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"have reasoned ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"that the law","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"as it stands","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"plainly covers sexual orientation and gender identity","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"because discrimination against them is based on generalizations about sex","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"that have nothing to do with their ability","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"to do their jobs .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"They also argue","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"that they were fired","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"for not conforming to sex stereotypes , a form of sex discrimination","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"that the Supreme Court recognized 30 years ago .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":273,"left":172,"right":272,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":168,"right":171,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":139,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":0,"right":138,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":167,"left":144,"right":166,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":143,"left":142,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":3,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":140,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":140,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":147,"right":165,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":147,"left":9,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":165,"left":151,"right":164,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":148,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":15,"right":149,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":157,"right":163,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":157,"left":155,"right":156,"rel